-- Raiffeisen Hires Former UniCredit Executive Szalay-Berzeviczy
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-11-08T11:22:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-08/raiffeisen-hires-former-unicredit-executive-szalay-berzeviczy.html
Raiffeisen Bank International AG (RBI) 
hired Attila Szalay-Berzeviczy, a former executive at  UniCredit
SpA (UCG)  and former chairman of the Budapest Stock Exchange, as an
adviser at its central and eastern European securities unit.  Szalay-Berzeviczy, who will start work in Vienna on Feb. 1,
will also keep his position as an adviser for the  Warsaw Stock
Exchange (GPW) , Raiffeisen said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
